name: punycode_codec
desc:
Provides a Dart implementation of the Punycode encoding algorithm
specified in RFC 3492.

name: PunycodeCodec
desc: A codec for encoding and decoding strings using the Punycode algorithm.

name: decoder
desc: Returns the decoder of this, converting from T to S.

name: encoder
desc: Returns the encoder from S to T.

name: PunycodeDecoder
desc:
Converts a Punycode string of ASCII-only symbols to a string of
Unicode symbols.

name: convert
desc: Converts input and returns the result of the conversion.

name: toUnicode
desc:
Converts a Punycode string representing a domain name or an email address
to Unicode. Only the Punycoded parts of the input will be converted, i.e.
it doesn't matter if you call it on a string that has already been
converted to Unicode.

name: PunycodeEncoder
desc:
Converts a string of Unicode symbols (e.g. a domain name label) to a
Punycode string of ASCII-only symbols.

name: convert
desc: Converts input and returns the result of the conversion.

name: toAscii
desc:
Converts a Unicode string representing a domain name or an email address
to Punycode. Only the non-ASCII parts of the domain name will be
converted, i.e. it doesn't matter if you call it with a domain that's
already in ASCII

name: punycodeDecoder
desc: The canonical version of the Punycode Decoder

name: punycodeEncoder
desc: The canonical version of the Punycode Encoder
